As topic says;

Pressing cancel on the 'editor' gives me;

Could not execute editor
Completed with errors, see above.

As far as I know, cancelling is not an error.

We have a locally hosted Stash server configured on our LAN with address http://servername.domain.local:7990/. After upgrading to SourceTree 1.6, when I select "Show Hosted Repositories" from the View menu the "Hosted Repositories" window opens along with a dialog window stating:

{quote}
Login failed for your Stash account.

The remote service said: 'Unable to connect to the remote server'
{quote}

When I click "Close" on the dialog window I get a new dialog stating:

{quote}
SourceTree has stopped working

A problem caused the program to stop working correctly...
{quote}

I then have the option to "Debug" or "Close program."

Pulling from the Stash server still works fine.
